Html:
Hi there,<br />
<br />
I'm using the mvvmlight toolkit in my application, and the the ViewModelLocator for changing views.<br />
The navigation is done in this way:<br />
In the MainViewModel i have a property called CurrentViewModel<br />
<pre><code>public ViewModelBase CurrentViewModel
readonly static EntryViewModel entryViewModel = new EntryViewModel();
readonly static GoodsReceiptViewModel goodsReceiptViewModel = new GoodsReceiptViewModel();</code></pre>

Which i assign to a ViewModel when i want to change the View:<br />
<pre><code>            switch (sView)
            {
                case &quot;EntryView&quot;:
                    this.CurrentViewModel = entryViewModel;
                    entryViewModel.Load();
</code></pre>

And My App.xaml:<br />
<pre><code>      &lt;vm:ViewModelLocator x:Key=&quot;Locator&quot; d:IsDataSource=&quot;True&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;DataTemplate DataType=&quot;{x:Type vm:EntryViewModel}&quot;&gt;
                &lt;views:EntryView /&gt;
            &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;
            &lt;DataTemplate DataType=&quot;{x:Type vm:GoodsReceiptViewModel}&quot;&gt;
                &lt;views:GoodsReceiptView /&gt;
            &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;</code></pre>

The problem is that when i change from one view to another the animations start to get &quot;confused&quot; causes an exception when raising a property change. <br />
XAML:<br />
<pre><code>                &lt;Storyboard&gt;
                    &lt;DoubleAnimationUsingKeyFrames Storyboard.TargetProperty=&quot;(UIElement.RenderTransform).(TransformGroup.Children)[3].(TranslateTransform.X)&quot; Storyboard.TargetName=&quot;gridMain&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;EasingDoubleKeyFrame KeyTime=&quot;0&quot; Value=&quot;196.5&quot;/&gt;
                    &lt;/DoubleAnimationUsingKeyFrames&gt;
                &lt;/Storyboard&gt;
</code></pre>

The exception is the folowing:<br />
<br />
&quot;gridMain name cannot be found in the name scope of 'System.Windows.Controls.Grid'&quot;<br />
<br />
Is there any other ways for changing views? Does anyone have an ideia why this error occurs?<br />
<br />
Thanks,<br />
